  "body": "### Component\n\nForge\n\n### Describe the feature you would like\n\nI'd like to be able to write some data (mostly deployed addresses) to a JSON file from a (solidity) script and be able to edit that file from another (solidity) script (i.e. add another key-value pair) without any knowledge of the JSON structure from the former script.\r\n\r\nMy understanding from the doc strings in the code is that the runtime keeps an in-memory JSON indexed by a key, but I haven't found a way to read a JSON, assign it to an in-memory index and extend it.\n\n### Additional context\n\n_No response_",
